uage acquisition focus on age as a fixed biological or chronological variable to encompass its social dimensions. What emerges is a more complex and nuanced understanding of age as it intersects with language learning in a way that links it fundamentally to other social phenomena, such as gender, ethnicity and social class.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aLanguage and culture. 0aLanguage and languages -- Age differences. 0aLanguage and languagesxAge differences. 0aLanguage and languages. 0aSecond language acquisitionxAge differences. 0aSecond language acquisition. 0aSociolinguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh  aEFL .  aL2 learners.  aSLA.  aSecond Language Acquisition.  aage and foreign language learning.  aage and second language.  aage factor.  aimpact of age on language learning.  aolder language learners.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769615140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847696151423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847696151/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK